{
  "text": "In our study, males and females were never found to share nests during the nonbreeding season. It is thus possible that they maintain exclusive ranges at this time of year. [CITATION_1] suggested that, because female A. sylvaticus share nests during the nonbreeding season, they do not maintain exclusive ranges then.",
